God you people can be fucking dense sometimes.  The fact that your parents were married was irrelevant, that's my whole point.  You're just supporting it.  In your case it wasn't DNA/biology that established your parents claim to custody, but it wasn't their marriage either, which is my point.  If your parents were unmarried and living together, and then separated, or if they were married, and separated, there would be no difference in how the children would be divided.  That's my point, the marriage is not relevant.  Child custody is separate from the marriage contract.<br>
