<br>
With adoption, in most cases, only one person can be the adoptive parent unless the two parents are married - there has been some move in Canada to broaden this to same sex/common law partners of the adoptive parent (called second parent adoption) though I wouldn't be surprised if this isn't the case in the states.  Biological parents can give up custody by putting a child up for adoption and a new person can gain custody by adoption.<br>
<br>
So at the end of the day, the state has decreed that the best interest of the child is supreme, but they are loathe to interfere with the biological &quot;rights&quot; unless someone pushes the issue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1347<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/8/03 12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=122.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abolish Marriage</span><hr size=1> What Backster said...<br>
<br>
Biology/DNA is a huge factor, best interest of the child is a huge factor, marriage contract is not a factor.<br>
